  "prompt": "Is Niacin added in the preparation of cannabis?",
  "response": "Niacin, also known as vitamin B3, is not a commonly added ingredient in the preparation of cannabis for consumption. Cannabis is typically consumed in various forms such as flower, edibles, oils, or tinctures, and its preparation usually focuses on methods that maximize its active compounds, such as cannabinoids (like THC and CBD) and terpenes.\n\nIn some contexts, like nutritional supplements or fortified foods, niacin may be included for health benefits, but it is not a standard additive in cannabis preparations. If you come across a cannabis product that lists niacin as an ingredient, it may be part of a specific formulation aimed at certain health benefits, but this is not typical for traditional cannabis products.\n\nAlways check the product label for specific ingredients and consult with a healthcare professional if you have questions about health impacts or interactions.",
